                        Attlee
                    )Sent to London as Department’s
                        telegram 5150, with the instruction: “Kindly transmit following message from
                        the President to PriMin.”</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d499</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">499</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-07-02T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-07-02T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="499" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/7–246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="94" xml:id="d499fn94">Sent to London as Department’s
                        telegram 5150, with the instruction: “Kindly transmit following message from
                        the President to <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss>.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-02T19:00:00-04:00">July 2, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to your message of June 28,<note n="95" xml:id="d499fn95">See undated
                        telegram, <ref target="#pg_639">p. 639</ref>.</note> I join with you in
                    regretting that drastic action is considered necessary by the mandatory
                    government while discussions of the report of the Anglo-American Committee are
                    in progress. I also join with you in a hope that law and order will be
                    maintained by the inhabitants of Palestine while efforts are being made toward a
                    solution of the long term policy.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
